      "timeline": {
        "years": "2013-2028",
        "description": "Elephant Park forms part of the Elephant & Castle regeneration area in south London, situated on the site of the former Heygate housing estate, which consisted of tower blocks built in the 1960s and 1970s, with a complex transport network, and which had gained a notorious reputation due to social factors and systemic neglect \nsystemic factors, which were exacerbated by the estate’s urban structure.Elephant Park most closely resembles a densely built-up, mixed-use neighbourhood in the spirit of the Compact City model and the 5-minute City concept. Its distinguishing feature is its compact structure: intensive \nuse of land for housing, services and green spaces, with a clear priority given to local service and recreational functions. It also provides excellent transport links and mobility for pedestrians and cyclists, which is typical of Compact City developments."
      },
