        "greenSpacePercentage": "39%",
        "buildingTypes": "The development is dominated by blocks of dense housing (rectangular or trapezoidal in plan); the areas within the blocks are raised by one storey and converted into semi-public green spaces; within the development comprising these blocks, there is at least one high-rise building that serves as a prominent landmark",
        "transport": "The redevelopment project covers the road and pedestrian network around the district, including plans to modernise and rebuild the underground station. The layout of the buildings and internal streets has been designed to improve pedestrian and cycling access in the area, thereby encouraging the use of public transport, bicycles and walking routes. There are numerous public transport stops and safe cycle paths in the area. The volume of car traffic has been minimised and the number of parking spaces reduced.‘, ’reducing emissions, promoting  sustainable transport‘, ’Prioritising cycling as the main mode of transport"
